ptions made by earlier philosophers but rather from the usage and functioning of examples in philosophical discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aExample. 0aParadigm (Theory of knowledge). 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780791488126423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780791488126/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles